<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-92-0205 </DOCNO><TEXT>The first national conference to help school and college administratorssolve mounting asbestos and other hazardous-materials problems will beheld April 21-22 in Philadelphia. Experts including toxicologist, schoolcompliance managers, hazardous materials training specialists, governmentofficials, environmental and occupational health consultants, and others,will present in detail: how to avoid hazardous materials accidents, injuries,illnesses, fires and explosions; how to fully meet the new OSHA, EPA,and most rigorous state regulations; how to prevent tort liabilitiesand claims involving employees and students; and how to meet public responsibilitiesfor personal and environmental safety and health.</TEXT></DOC>